More than half the respondents (65%) had emergency contact numbers in their mobile phones, but 73.1% of them had password protected phones. Emergency numbers could be accessed in only 22.6% of those phones through the lock-screen. In case the mobile phone network broke down, 37.4% of the respondents stated they would use a landline telephone to contact their family, 32.5% said they would return home, and 4% reported that they had a pre-planned place to meet their family members during a disaster. 


